-- Acerinox, Telefonica Top Holdings of Spain’s Rich, Cinco Says
-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e
-- 2013-08-13T08:01:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-13/acerinox-telefonica-top-holdings-of-spain-s-rich-cinco-says.html
Stainless-steel manufacturer
Acerinox, followed by telephone co. and pharmaceutical maker
Almirall are biggest holdings in private investment funds run by
 Spain ’s richest families, Cinco Dias reported.
*Acerinox appears in six of 13 Sicav funds owned by families of
Alicia Koplowitz, Juan Abello, Manuel Jove, Ramchand Bhavnani,
Rosalia Mera and the Del Pinos, among others, newspaper reports,
citing 1H investment filings
*Spanish fortunes overall increased holdings in domestic stocks,
with Bhavnani more than doubling his compared with 2H 2012,
report says
*13 funds held about eu1.5b at end 1H 2013, including foreign
equities and other securities, Cinco Dias says.  To contact the reporter on this story:
